But Hare denied that the YMCA had a cultural issue that prevented staff from reporting Lord&#39;s child safety violations.
Staff said they observed violations, including Lord being alone with children, babysitting them privately, letting them sit on his lap, telling one he loved it and letting children play with his cell phone .
Danielle Ockwell, whose supervisor was Lord and who had requested child protection training because she was concerned about his behavior, testified that the children&#39;s director, Jacqui Barnat, who was Lord&#39;s supervisor at the YMCA Caringbah, was &quot;very intimidating and most of the time was very unapproachable&quot;.
