However, Internet connections below three kilometers for surfing, exchanging emails, text messages or downloading data remain prohibited, the authority explained.
Passengers are asked to put their smartphones, tablets and other devices into flight mode.
So still no Words With Friends, the Scrabble-like online game that actor Alec Baldwin was playing on his smartphone in 2011 when he was publicly forced off an American Airlines jet for refusing to turn off the device while the aircraft was parked at the gate.
And heavier equipment such as laptops still need to be stowed, as there is a risk of injury if they fly through the cabin.
Cell phone calls during the flight also remain prohibited.
The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) has regulatory authority over telephone calls, not the FAA.
