This is really a must for our country.
&quot;It&#39;s not something that we will possibly use,&quot; said Hasan Ikhrata, executive director of the Southern California Assn. of Governments, which plans to record mileage for all California drivers in the state by 2025.
The way we pay these taxes will change.
The technology is there.
The initiative comes at a time when the Highway Trust Fund, which is funded by taxes Americans pay at the gas pump, is broke.
But in America people don&#39;t fill up as much as they used to.
Cars use less petrol.
